---
import { GH_URL } from '../consts';
import TerminalWindow from './TerminalWindow.astro';

const demo = [
  `<span class="m">$</span> <span class="b">unread</span> <span class="a">@thehackernews</span> <span class="m">--last-days 14</span>`,
  `<span class="c">→</span> Resolved <span class="b">The Hacker News</span> <span class="c">(channel)</span>`,
  `<span class="c">→</span> Fetched 99 new messages from Telegram`,
  `<span class="c">→</span> Running analysis... 4 chunks <span class="c">(gpt-5.4-mini)</span>`,
  `<span class="c">→</span> Wrote <span class="a">~/.unread/reports/the-hacker-news/<wbr/>summary-2026-05-23.md</span>`,
  `   <span class="c">$0.016 · 18s</span>`,
  ``,
  `<span class="b">## TL;DR</span>`,
  `Active exploitation and supply-chain compromise dominated`,
  `the period: KEV-listed flaws, repeated abuse of npm/PyPI/`,
  `GitHub workflows, attacker speed outpacing patching.`,
  ``,
  `<span class="b">## Worth checking</span>`,
  `- <span class="a">[#8980]</span> Mini Shai-Hulud worm — GitHub OIDC + cache poisoning`,
  `- <span class="a">[#9008]</span> Cisco SD-WAN CVE-2026-20182 — active exploit, CISA KEV`,
  `- <span class="a">[#9063]</span> Megalodon — 5,561 repos compromised in 6 hours`,
].join('\n');
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-text">
      <h1>Read your unread.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I had 50 Telegram channels I'd never read. Now I read one Markdown summary a week —
        every claim links back to the message, paragraph, or timestamp it came from.
        Same thing works on <strong>YouTube videos, web pages, PDFs, and stdin</strong>.
      </p>
      <div class="ctas">
        <a href="#quickstart" class="btn btn-primary">
          Install in 30 seconds
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href={GH_URL} class="btn btn-ghost" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 .5a12 12 0 0 0-3.8 23.4c.6.1.8-.3.8-.6v-2c-3.3.7-4-1.6-4-1.6-.5-1.4-1.3-1.7-1.3-1.7-1.1-.8.1-.8.1-.8 1.2.1 1.8 1.2 1.8 1.2 1.1 1.9 2.9 1.3 3.6 1 .1-.8.4-1.3.8-1.6-2.7-.3-5.5-1.3-5.5-6 0-1.3.5-2.4 1.2-3.3-.1-.3-.5-1.5.1-3.2 0 0 1-.3 3.3 1.3a11.5 11.5 0 0 1 6 0c2.3-1.6 3.3-1.3 3.3-1.3.7 1.7.3 2.9.1 3.2.8.9 1.2 2 1.2 3.3 0 4.7-2.8 5.7-5.5 6 .4.3.8 1 .8 2v3c0 .3.2.7.8.6A12 12 0 0 0 12 .5z"/></svg>
          Star on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="footnote">
        Open source (Apache&nbsp;2.0). Runs on macOS, Linux, Windows. Your data stays on your disk.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-demo">
      <TerminalWindow title="~"><Fragment set:html={demo} /></TerminalWindow>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 4.5rem 0 3rem;
  }
  .hero-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 1.1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
    .hero { padding-top: 3rem; }
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin: 0 0 1.6rem;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .lead strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 600; }
  .ctas {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }
  .footnote {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
</style>
